    • Constructor Detail

      • Message

        public Message(int identifier,
       java.lang.Object args1,
       java.lang.Object args2)
        The Message contains up to two Objects of any class. The identifier is used to identify the message and to typecast the Objects back to there original classtype.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier, MUST BE one of the constant fields of message, all other identifiers are ignored
        args1 - an object
        args2 - an object
